# Clinic Appointment API

This project is a simple Clinic Appointment API built using FastAPI and Docker.
## Laboratory Context
This project was developed in an offline Windows 11 laboratory environment.
Python was not installed directly on the computer. The application was executed using Docker and
prebuilt Docker image named clinic-fastapi-base:1.0.
## Features
Create clinic appointments
- View all appointments
View one appointment
Update appointment details
- Cancel appointments
## Technologies Used
- Python
FastAPІ
Docker
Git
## How to Run
docker compose up --build
a
Open http://localhost:8000/docs.

## Authentication

This section describes the basic token security added to the API. 

### Test Account 
- Username: admin  
- Password: clinic123 
- Token: clinic-secret-token 

### API Endpoints 
- `POST /login` — Public. Submit your credentials here to get your token. 
- `GET /` — Public. Welcome page. 

- All appointment routes (`GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE`) and `/me` now require you to provide the bearer token. 

### Educational Limitations 
**Note:** This configuration is strictly for learning purposes in class. It hardcodes data and does not expire tokens. A real-world production system must use safe password hashing, proper databases, expiring tokens (like JWT), and HTTPS to protect patient privacy.

## Logout

This API does not have a real logout endpoint because the server does not store tokens anywhere — it only checks if the token matches the hardcoded value. Since there is no session or database record to delete, there is nothing to "destroy" on logout.

In a real production system, logout would work by storing tokens in a database and deleting the record when the user logs out, or by using JWT tokens with an expiration time so they automatically become invalid after a set period.